                            <comment id="13776911" author="hudson" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 00:25:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Mahout-Quality #2266 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2266/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2266/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1342&quot; title=&quot;Exclude .git/**, Eclipse, and .patch files from Rat check&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-1342&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-1342&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Exclude git repo files, Eclipse IDE specific files and patch files from RAT check (sslavic: rev 1526047)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/mahout/trunk/pom.xml&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13776930" author="sslavic" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 00:43:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch is applied, thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mpercy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mpercy&quot;&gt;Mike Percy&lt;/a&gt; for providing it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw, I&apos;m finding &lt;a href=&quot;http://creadur.apache.org/rat/apache-rat-plugin/check-mojo.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;apache-rat-plugin check-mojo docs&lt;/a&gt; to be confusing.&lt;br/&gt;
For parameter &lt;tt&gt;excludes&lt;/tt&gt; docs state:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specifies files, which are excluded in the report. By default, no files are excluded.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While for parameter &lt;tt&gt;useDefaultExcludes&lt;/tt&gt; of the same mojo docs state:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether to use the default excludes when scanning for files. The default excludes are:&lt;br/&gt;
meta data files for version control systems&lt;br/&gt;
temporary files used by Maven, see useMavenDefaultExcludes&lt;br/&gt;
configuration files for Eclipse, see useEclipseDefaultExcludes&lt;br/&gt;
configuration files for IDEA, see useIdeaDefaultExcludes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Default value is: true.&lt;br/&gt;
User property is: rat.useDefaultExcludes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &lt;tt&gt;useDefaultExcludes&lt;/tt&gt; being true by default was respected, I expect that we would not have to configure excludes for svn, maven, eclipse and idea files. Also I expect that specifying (additional) &lt;tt&gt;excludes&lt;/tt&gt; should not be turning off &lt;tt&gt;useDefaultExcludes&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776977" author="mpercy" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 01:16:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the commit Stevo!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Interesting point... looking at another project I contribute to (Flume) we have a laundry list of Rat excludes as well, not sure what happens with the default excludes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13778050" author="sslavic" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 21:41:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving as implemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/RAT-107&quot; title=&quot;useEclipseDefaultExcludes does not ignore sub-module&amp;#39;s eclipse dotfiles.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;RAT-107&quot;&gt;RAT-107&lt;/a&gt; is fixed, we will be able to further improve plugin configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
